research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Nocona, Texas, is a Type A general law city governed by a Mayor and five Councilmen. Christopher Nunneley is the current Mayor, and Robert Fuller serves as Mayor Pro Tem. The Council Members include Yesika Rodriguez, Chuck Hittle, Matthew D. Fenoglio, and Robert E. Norman. Newly elected councilors, including Chuck Hittle, Chris Nunneley, and Yesika Rodriguez, took office in November 2024, with Robert Fuller also elected as Mayor Pro Tem at that time. Christopher Nunneley ran for Mayor in the November 2025 election.
